I'd rather have you spend the rest of the year reading books that will make you better at executing a startup successfully.  

The goal is not VC.  The goal is to AVOID VC.

@Austen Another reason why founders should bootstrap in almost all cases.  

Insane that you can screw your own company through funding rounds rather than execution.

If you raise, you should still have the bootstrap mentality,  and make the round last - https://t.co/McQXzgYHTr

@GetWiser @paulg Copying your competitors here or there is fine, but as a general focus/strategy it is absolutely terrible.  

Whoever is closest to the customer, wins.  

This will become self-evident when you start talking to customers a LOT &amp; understand how many problems you can solve.

@gdb Good ideas are a dime a dozen.  Get me together with my entrepreneur buddies, and we come up 10 really good ideas over a lunch.  

Execution is the true differentiator.  

https://t.co/LFGzFNZQfp

@VedikaBhaia Nothing wrong with being afraid for your startup to fail IMO, so long as it provides you with motivational fuel to work harder.

Some of the startups I've worried most about, the ones that kept me up at night, turned out to be the most successful.

